NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display Light' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display Light'.

Walbaum Display Light Regular (walbaumdisp-lt-rg.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display Light' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display Light'.

Walbaum Display Regular (walbaumdisp-rg.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Walbaum Display Regular' ≠ 'Walbaum Display' (NID 1).

MS NID 16/17

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Walbaum Display Regular' ≠ 'Walbaum Display' (NID 1).

Walbaum Display Italic (walbaumdisp-it.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WalbaumDisplay-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. You can learn more about Monotype here: www.monotype.com

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. Walbaum Display Italic (walbaumdisp-it.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display Italic' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Walbaum Display Italic (walbaumdisp-it.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display Italic' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).

NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display SemiBold' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display SemiBold'.

Walbaum was meticulously crafted by Monotype’s Carl Crossgrove, Charles Nix, Juan Villanueva and Lynn Yun to bring Justus Erich Walbaum’s high contrast Didone style masterpiece to the 21st century. Walbaum has over 600 glyphs with OpenType typographic features like small capitals, old style and lining figures, proportional and tabular figures, fractions and ligatures. Also included in the family are three decorative and ornament fonts.'

Walbaum Display SemiBold Italic (walbaumdisp-sb-it.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WalbaumDisplaySemiBold-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WalbaumDisplaySemiBold-Italic', Everything looks good.

Mac NID 6

Walbaum Display Bold (walbaumdisp-bd.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display Bold' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Bold'.

Walbaum Display Bold (walbaumdisp-bd.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WalbaumDisplay-Bold', Everything looks good.

Walbaum Display Bold (walbaumdisp-bd.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display Bold' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Bold'.

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'WalbaumDisplay-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Mac NID 16/17

NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display Bold Italic' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Bold Italic'.

Walbaum Display Heavy Regular (walbaumdisp-hv-rg.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WalbaumDisplayHeavy', Everything looks good.

Mac NID 6

Walbaum Display Heavy Italic (walbaumdisp-hv-it.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WalbaumDisplayHeavy-Italic', Everything looks good.

Walbaum Display Heavy Italic (walbaumdisp-hv-it.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Walbaum' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Display Heavy Italic' = NID 1 'Walbaum Display Heavy' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

Pass

Walbaum Display Light Regular (walbaumdisp-lt-rg.ttf)

GPOS

kern

Simple check if kern feature in GPOS table.

The font has GPOS kerning.

Warning

Walbaum Display Light Regular (walbaumdisp-lt-rg.ttf)

kern

-/-

Check if 'kern' table in TTF font.

Font has 'kern' table. Please verify if font requires kern table or if only GPOS kerning should be in font.
For example: PowerPoint only supports a flat GPOS kerning or a kern table. So, if the customer requires PowerPoint support, a kern table is necessary.
